This adds a `.sessionReauth` method which is pretty straightforward, very similar to the existing `.signIn` method.

There's also a preparatory commit that rejiggers the way we do mock responses, to more effectively test the "incorrect email case" retry loop for both `/account/login` and `/session/reauth`.  These tests required the ability to have two mock responses in flight at once, because the client makes two requests during the function under test.  What I've done here *seems* to be OK but I don't really know this repo very well, so it might have unintended side-effects...

